Is your gungame server filled with gg_aim_shotty clones like mine? Well, mash them all together into a single map. Players start unable to fire upon each other until one person enters the center area via teleport (modified from Biuxify's spritetrail prefrab) and chooses one of the 12 aim shottys (hence the map name) by pressing the red button in front of the picture of the map. There are also 2 secret aim shottys to choose from if you can find them. 

Choices include:
-gg_aim_shotty created by -=][-][=-Silent
    The original that started all these maps.
-gg_sewer_shotty created by Dr. Kepper
    An aim shotty with an underwater area where the ground normally is
-gg_heavy_shotty created by (unknown)
    An aim shotty with a basement area
-gg_shotty_snow created by fiasco
    An aim shotty with a snow theme with a taller central area and middle passage 
-gg_shotty_suburb created by soulsz
    An aim shotty with a suburban theme with a modified upper level that you can get to the top of.
-gg_cbble_shotty created by festea
    A larger aim shotty with a cbble theme and large central building.
-gg_wow_shotty created by The Naked Stick
    A more circular spooky shotty made for warriors of war clan (that I am also in)
-gg_momentum_shotty created by Dr. Kepper
    A duplicate of aim shotty with a warehouse theme. The boxes and side walls move up and down ever 5 seconds.
-gg_glass_shotty created by Dr. Kepper
    A duplicate of aim shotty with a glass theme. Give wallhacks to everyone.
-gg_halo_shotty created by Dr. Kepper
    A duplicate of aim shotty with a halo theme. Everyone also has half gravity. Halo textures by [-B-]
-gg_hell_shotty created by Dr. Kepper
    A duplicate of aim shotty with a fire theme. There are many ramps that launch players to the other side to speed up game play and increase movement. Also, fall damage has been disabled.
-gg_simpson_arena_vi created by RattenHaus
    A simpson theme map that has a layout pretty similar to shotty, but the center area stairs are directly in front and the sides of the map are less open.

SECRET SHOTTYS
-gg_rave_shotty created by Dr. Kepper
    An aim shotty duplicate complete with disco balls, neon textures by shox, and some music by the East Clubberz
-gg_sonic_shotty created by Dr. Kepper
    An aim shotty duplicate with a blue metal texture theme with textures created by .Eric, a rotating Sonic model created by (unkown), and players move twice as fast.

If you upload this to your server or use part of it for your map please post here, I'd love to hear about it. Also reviews are greatly appreciated.

The name of this map is "gg_105th".
====================================

The concept behind the design of this map is to create a fun [Gun Game](http://css.gamebanana.com/maps/cats/8026 "Gun Game") style map to play on. This version of the map (v1.0) is brushed with develop textures which many Gun Game players enjoy. This map was originally released for [Day of Defeat: Source](http://dods.gamebanana.com/ "Day of Defeat: Source"). Some changes to the map where made. All of the control points have been removed. Approximately 20 of the original props have been removed or replaced. Some new blocks and features have been implemented to fit the Gun Game style of playing. The over all cosmetic structure of this map have remained authentic to the official release ([dod_105th](http://dods.gamebanana.com/maps/183715 "dod_105th")).

The password to the downloadable archive is "**gamebanana**".

Thank you for viewing my release.
---------------------------------

1024 cubed is a perfect cube with an internal dimension of 1024 units on each side.  There are multiple levels and it is symmetrical and balanced.  You can jump from the spawn to the basement pool or take multiple ladders to access any floor quickly.  It's a very bright map but less bright in the pool level.

All 36 spawn points work correctly, it's a small file and nav file included.  No buy zones included.

Map Title          : Pool (with HDR)
Map Version        : v1.0 Final
Author             : dark_webber
Website            : NA

============================

Game               : Counter Strike Source
Supported Gametype : Gun Game
Map Size           : 18 players (9vs9)

============================

Contents of this Package : This is a custom map made for CSS, wich takes place at a pool house.

============================

Installation Instructions : Copy pool.bsp to the folder C:\Program Files\Valve\SteamApps\[username]\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps where Valve is you installation directory and username is your Steam account username.

============================

Construction Date  : 4/5/2008
Construction Time  : 4 days
Computer Configuration : INTEL DUALCORE 6750, 2Gb Ram
Custom Content     : map
Known Bugs         : NA

============================

Credit to Authors  : NA
Special Thanks     : NA
Additional Notes   : NA

============================

This is a Gun Game style map, one of a larger/medium size. It's reminiscent of textured city and a few others in small ways but otherwise completely original, especially in layout. I wanted to create a colorful map with plenty of room and obstacles, so here it is. 20 players per team (40 total).

Medium size
16 + 16 spots for CTs and Ts
Fairly balanced map
Fully textured and decorated
Full navmesh by hand

Suitable for Deathmatch and Gungame

In this small fast paced map, you can choose to play it with the gun game add-on or just a deathmatch with friends or complete strangers.
This map has 4 rooms, 2 secret hallways, a basement for underground fighting, and now a top area for aerial assaults. 
Creates and boxes add extra hiding and assaulting the enemy team. 

Please provide constructive criticism.

New/Changed Features:
-Added access to the top through a large connecting room around the map
-Changed the large doorway a split it into two smaller doorways for less spawn killing

Note- There were many new features with the prev version of the map (The first release online was version 1.0, this is now 1.25)
I'll post the link to download the other versions later, when I get them uploaded.

Install notes-
 1) Unzip gg_unknownfight
 2) Take the maps folder and move it to the Steam Dir/(your username)/counter strike source/cstrike/
 3) Play

This is an entirely original map. The idea and layout is similar to some obvious others, but it's a bit unique in that it was built from scratch. It's a fy arena style for Gun Game and I thought it would be fun to throw something like this together for a little variation to the usual. I think it's a good balance of open spaces and covered areas.

Based on (aka a remake of) simpsons_h1. This was built from scratch. I did not decompile the original, I simply played on the map as a reference. A few things are different and I've added some space to make the map more "breathable" than its predecessor. I've included dev notes. (much thanks to Ryan's Dev; the colors are fun)

Comments/suggestions are welcome!

I took the lego MAFIA arena and decompiled it. I thought this would look nice as a textured map with some ryan dev textures (gj on your pack, ryan) so I made some very slight spacing adjustments after resetting all the geometry, as well as added a couple extras.

Based on BA_ATTACKLOCKDOWN by teh_mapn00b. Same layout, some additions, a different skybox and using the dev textures. Special thanks are included. I take only credit for the remake and the additions. Fun!

This is a pretty basic remake of textured city advanced. I readjusted the lighting (added some colored lights as well) all around the map, made some small adjustments to the blocks, added glass to the windows and retextured it with my custom, simple textures. I wanted to get rid of the orange/gray and just go for the gray shades so it would be a bit easier on the eyes.

This is really mostly a copy of textured city advanced with a ton of small changes. The most obvious is the retexturing, some are custom block textures I made myself, some are from ryan_dev, and the rest is just colored lighting. I did make some fun stuff, like breakable things (mostly windows), slightly enhanced ladder access, a few spots are just prettied up a bit. I thought this would be a great alternative to the standard crosshatch look to all the others (or the grey and orange, blegh).

Some notes: skybox - I think this one was by KAMAOKC, but I'm not sure. I can't seem to find it again to give props. Same goes for the glass texture I used. I wish I kept better track of this stuff.

If you see my previous map, this is the same exact thing, only I've made it night time. Texture city at night? I haven't seen a good one yet and wanted to try it out. I'm happy with the results. :)
